{
  "text": "ERp44 binds to substrates via its nonclassical CXXS active-site motif (2), which lacks a resolving cysteine and therefore renders these intermolecular disulfide adducts longer-lived than typical catalytic complexes. Moreover, despite its C-terminal ER retrieval signal ERp44 is atypically enriched in the ERGolgi intermediate compartment (ERGIC)/cis-Golgi [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , which favors a model in which ERp44 retrieves substrates from ERGIC/cis-Golgi to ER.",
